  "bib_entries": {
    "18996778": {
      "title": "Superconformal black hole quantum mechanics",
      "abstract": "In recent work, the superconformal quantum mechanics describing D0 branes in the AdS2 × S2 × CY3 attractor geometry of a Calabi-Yau black hole with D4 brane charges pA has been constructed and found to contain a large degeneracy of chiral primary bound states. In this paper it is shown that the asymptotic growth of chiral primaries for N D0 branes exactly matches the Bekenstein-Hawking area law for a black hole with D4 brane charge pA and D0 brane charge N. This large degeneracy arises from D0 branes in lowest Landau levels which tile the CY3 × S2 horizon. It is conjectured that such a multi-D0 brane CFT1 is holographically dual to IIA string theory on AdS2 × S2 × CY3."
    }
